        <section class="welcome">
            <h1>About this Website</h1>
            <p>This website serves as a platform to be able to add/edit/update a course list database. 
                Each course contains a course code, a name, a syllabus link, and a progression level.</p>
            <p>The database server used for this website is SQLite3.</p>
            <h2>Conclusions</h2>
            <p>Throughout the development of this website, several conclusions were drawn:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>SQLite3 is a lightweight and efficient database solution for small to medium-scale web applications. It was very easy to start using this one!</li>
                <li>Express.js provides a framework for building web servers and handling HTTP requests.</li>
                <li>Using EJS as the view engine allows for dynamic content generation and reuse of HTML templates.</li>
                <li>Client-side and server-side validation are essential for ensuring data integrity and preventing errors.</li>
                <li>Proper error handling and feedback mechanisms enhance the user experience and provide helpful guidance in case of issues.</li>
            </ul>

        </section>
